291
00:19:45,306 --> 00:19:47,122
-Oh, my.
-Yeah.

292
00:19:47,917 --> 00:19:53,681
And he's funny--not just his humor,
but the way he looks at the world.

293
00:19:54,055 --> 00:19:57,490
I mean he can turn everything and show it to you in a whole new way.

294
00:19:58,496 --> 00:20:01,473
And he's got such a strong sense of what's right and...

295
00:20:01,565 --> 00:20:05,280
He's so quick to learn and so eager to connect with other people.

296
00:20:09,445 --> 00:20:11,570
Like he's connected with you.

297
00:20:13,226 --> 00:20:14,872
With all of us.

298
00:20:17,165 --> 00:20:21,381
<i>Once again I was in a familiar place--
where my story began.</i>

299
00:20:22,147 --> 00:20:26,302
<i>But suddenly, like a flash,
the whole story fell into place.</i>

300
00:20:27,285 --> 00:20:29,782
<i>-Don't do this.
-Zzyx ordered you to exterminate him.</i>

301
00:20:29,788 --> 00:20:31,830
<i>I can't let either of you walk way.</i>

302
00:20:32,086 --> 00:20:35,492
<i>You were Bailen's mentor! He trusted you, and now you're working for them!</i>

303
00:20:35,517 --> 00:20:38,970
<i>No, no. Bailen gave up any claim on the boy when he turned his back on the company.</i>

304
00:20:38,978 --> 00:20:40,362
<i>They want the boy dead!</i>

305
00:20:50,646 --> 00:20:52,850
<i>I finally had a piece of the truth.</i>

306
00:20:53,166 --> 00:20:55,252
<i>Now it was time to get the rest.</i>

307
00:20:55,307 --> 00:20:57,383
It's all right. It' all right. Settle down.

308
00:20:57,486 --> 00:21:00,252
Listen to me. It's okay.

309
00:21:03,855 --> 00:21:06,223
I'm sorry about the chloroform.

310
00:21:07,288 --> 00:21:10,072
I tried to get the jump on you before and it wasn't pretty, so...

311
00:21:11,808 --> 00:21:15,880
I remember what happened...with Kern.

312
00:21:16,838 --> 00:21:20,211
The two of you were talking about Adam Bailen and something called Zzyx.

313
00:21:21,485 --> 00:21:25,592
Is that connected with the location I discovered in Bailen's papers? The logo?

314
00:21:27,885 --> 00:21:30,901
This is why I warned you to stop asking questions.

315
00:21:31,028 --> 00:21:33,182
You didn't bring me out here to lecture me.

316
00:21:34,687 --> 00:21:36,373
-No.
-Then why?

317
00:21:39,317 --> 00:21:41,421
Because I thought it would help you remember.

318
00:21:43,808 --> 00:21:45,372
Did you hear something?

319
00:21:47,577 --> 00:21:48,580
What?

320
00:21:56,287 --> 00:21:58,121
Get down! Get down! Go!

321
00:21:58,447 --> 00:22:00,723
Go! Aah!

322
00:22:02,575 --> 00:22:04,960
Are you all right? 
Come on. Give me your arm.

323
00:22:13,427 --> 00:22:15,812
Tom, get in! Get in!

324
00:22:18,897 --> 00:22:20,493
You don't know how to drive.

325
00:22:21,425 --> 00:22:22,543
Hold on.

326
00:22:25,036 --> 00:22:26,303
Go!

327
00:22:45,285 --> 00:22:46,701
Hey.

328
00:22:47,277 --> 00:22:48,822
What are you doing here?

329
00:22:49,395 --> 00:22:54,913
