not caring if Kyle was here or not.

334
00:23:12,715 --> 00:23:15,750
-And now that he might leave--
-He's not going anywhere.

335
00:23:17,475 --> 00:23:20,401
-You sound like Josh.
-He's got a life here.

336
00:23:21,316 --> 00:23:26,982
A trippy, no-memory, messed-up life,
but it's still a life.

337
00:23:28,076 --> 00:23:32,033
He's not gonna throw that away for two people he has no memory of ever knowing.

338
00:23:34,575 --> 00:23:36,642
How can you be so sure?

339
00:23:39,946 --> 00:23:42,653
Because the other ending to that story is...

340
00:23:42,928 --> 00:23:45,212
It's not something I'm willing to accept.

341
00:23:55,255 --> 00:23:57,553
You should've let me take you to the hospital.

342
00:23:57,806 --> 00:23:59,853
I'll take care of that.
Get out of here. Go.

343
00:23:59,916 --> 00:24:02,583
I'm not getting out of this car until you've
told me everything.

344
00:24:03,428 --> 00:24:05,182
You know most of it already.

345
00:24:06,908 --> 00:24:08,530
We were in the woods.

346
00:24:10,076 --> 00:24:14,030
We were surprise by Kern and...

347
00:24:14,925 --> 00:24:18,521
And I killed him.
Because he was gonna kill you.

348
00:24:18,988 --> 00:24:22,620
By the time I was done getting rid of the body, you'd woken up and you...

349
00:24:23,408 --> 00:24:27,500
You wandered into the city and got put in juvenile detention.

350
00:24:29,295 --> 00:24:33,432
And once Nicole Trager took you in, I...

351
00:24:33,817 --> 00:24:39,021
I just figured it was smarter to...
keep an eye on you.

352
00:24:39,025 --> 00:24:40,543
Tell me more.

353
00:24:40,907 --> 00:24:43,181
Tell me why people want me dead.

354
00:24:43,358 --> 00:24:48,393
Tell me why that test said that David and Julia Peterson were my parents when I don't remember anything about them.

355
00:24:49,848 --> 00:24:53,242
Why don't I remember anything before that night in the woods with Kern?

356
00:24:56,827 --> 00:24:58,660
Okay, I'll tell you.

357
00:24:59,355 --> 00:25:01,291
Now, should we be worried that he's not back yet?

358
00:25:01,298 --> 00:25:03,733
Oh, I think he got overwhelmed.
We'll talk to him.

359
00:25:03,778 --> 00:25:06,182
-We can try it again tomorrow.
-That would be great.

360
00:25:06,737 --> 00:25:09,451
-Okay. Thank you all for your time.
-You're welcome.

361
00:25:11,287 --> 00:25:13,381
-Kyle.
-Noah.

362
00:25:14,178 --> 00:25:17,092
-Where you been?
-You doing okay?

363
00:25:17,226 --> 00:25:21,140
<i>My mind was racing with the information I had just learned from Foss.</i>

364
00:25:21,545 --> 00:25:26,071
<i>Foss, my patron saint of lost pasts and confusing futures.</i>

365
00:25:26,198 --> 00:25:28,531
<i>Everyone was there in front of me.</i>

366
00:25:28,635 --> 00:25:33,471
<i>The family who took me in,
and the family who wanted to take me home.</i>

367
00:25:33,667 --> 00:25:37,203
<i>And right then, 
I knew exactly what I had to do.</i>

368
00:25:38,595 --> 00:25:40,151
I remember.

369
00:25:42,025 --> 00:25:46,282
Mom. Dad.

370
00:25:48,836 --> 00:25:50,620
I remember you.

371
00:26:03,577 --> 00:26:06,781
I remember the vacation we had when I was nine to Hawaii.

372
00:26:07,916 --> 00:26:10,160
I'd never seen a palm tree before.

373
00:26:11,148 --> 00:26:14,843
And you took me to the science museum where they had the whispering corridors.

374
00:26:16,017 --> 00:26:20,901
And we went sailing near the waterfall on the boat with the rainbow sail.

375
00:26:21,368 --> 00:26:24,642
And every night at the hotel I'd order the same thing for dessert.

376
00:26:25,167 --> 00:26:27,913
A banana split--hold the banana.

377
00:26:28,867 --> 00:26:32,243
Can you tell us what happened to you,
where you've been all this time?

378
00:26:33,505 --> 00:26:35,323
Still a blank.

379
00:26:38,085 --> 00:26:40,470
Well, once you get home,

380
00:26:40,476 --> 00:26:45,793
I'm sure you canfind a new therapist who can help him recover even more of his memory.

381
00:26:45,798 --> 00:26:49,553
-Why  can't you still be his therapist?
-Yeah, you know him better than anyone.

382
00:26:50,037 --> 00:26:51,662
No offense.

383
00:26:52,087 --> 00:26:54,693
The Petersons live in Connecticut.

384
00:26:57,158 --> 00:26:59,732
So, how soon before you leave?

385
00:27:00,426 --> 00:27:03,690
Well, we don't want to rush anything.

386
00:27:04,976 --> 00:27:07,231
I'll be ready to go by tomorrow.

387
00:27:23,737 --> 00:27:27,703
Now that I know, I'm ready.

388
00:27:28,828 --> 00:27:31,280
I can't believe he's leaving before I got to make out with him.

389
00:27:32,945 --> 00:27:34,270
Kidding.

390
00:27:35,538 --> 00:27:37,543
We should be happy for him.

391
00:27:37,658 --> 00:27:40,421
Keep telling yourself that, Sister Sunshine.

392
00:27:40,595 --> 00:27:42,991
I thought this was supposed to be a good-bye party.

393
00:27:43,546 --> 00:27:45,031
Woohoo.

394
00:27:48,897 --> 00:27:50,081
I just don't get it.

395
00:27:50,225 --> 00:27:54,253
You went from savant amnesia victim to banana split guy in two hours?

396
00:27:55,016 --> 00:27:56,962
It all just came rushing back.

397
00:27:57,397 --> 00:27:59,313
Dude, I put myself out for you.

398
00:27:59,517 --> 00:28:02,820
I kept your secrets,
screwed things up with Lori.

399
00:28:03,138 --> 00:28:07,143
I did everything I could to help you get to the bottom of the mystery, and now you're telling me it's done?

400
00:28:07,477 --> 00:28:08,580
Yes.

401
00:28:10,626 --> 00:28:12,360
There's something else going on here.

402
00:28:12,688 --> 00:28:14,330
Something you're not telling me about.

403
00:28:14,475 --> 00:28:16,591
You've proven you could keep my secrets.

404
00:28:16,757 --> 00:28:20,111
If there was anything to tell, don't you think I'd find a way to bring you in on it?

405
00:28:23,018 --> 00:28:24,301
